race.comment: ASHES TO ASHES (8) has a strong record here with two wins and two placings from six starts. Scored by half a length last time (20.68) in a Grade 5 over 365m at this track. Looks the one to beat with even luck. BLACK BEAR (6) has been out of the placings the last couple but was a Grade 5 winner (20.93) three back at this track. Has the ability and expected to do much better. CUMBRIA TESS (1) jumped from a low draw and boxed on well to finish second last time, beaten 0.8 lengths (20.95) behind Yuna Herrera at this track. Winning chance. CUMBRIA PETE (3) should bounce back after an unplaced effort here recently.
